  "text": "Formulations F1 (I and II), F8, and F9 were sticky powders despite the presence of granular mannitol which possessed improved flow and compressibility properties [CITATION_1] . The impairment of the flow properties of these powders was due to the high concentration of included PEG blend in the powder (4:1 and 4:0.75 granular mannitol:PEG, respectively). This caused the stickiness and softness of the mixture due to the low melting point (37°C) of the PEG blend.",
